name: Trish
text:
While the fields are nice, parking is a mess. It appears there are only 2 handicapped parking spots, neither of which is van accessible.  People were double parked in some areas,  and only by the grace of God did we find a spot where we had room to let out the wheelchair ramp.
It is possible it was such a mess because they had apparently double booked a field? One team was made to wait another 30 minutes, AND use a different field. What a challenge for parents with multiple children on different schedules.

One day this place will be nice. Until then, prepare to get very dirty.

name: Ciara Jones
text: My son had an 8u baseball tournament over the past weekend. We were told we had to park in the first parking lot (just a grass field)...7PM game...no lights, holes, ditches, unlevel, very unsafe for anyone. I turn in and my car hit a dip that I couldn't see, after parking I walk to my trunk and stepped into a hole, right foot sank past my ankle...I fell...AND I'M 4.5 MONTHS PREGNANT! I was told that the land is owned by the Houston county board of education. That park has been there way too long for it to still be the way it is! UNSAFE! ACCIDENTS WAITING TO HAPPEN, AND ME AND MY UNBORN WERE IT!
